{"type":"message","id":"fd010f30","parentId":"cff60ff0","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:13:02.942Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iqq7a5xhgsww_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    DEBUG = os.getenv('DEBUG', 'false').lower() == 'true'\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_env(cls):\n        return {k: v for k, v in vars(cls).items() \n                if k.isupper() and not k.startswith('_')}\n```\n## Best Practices\n- Never commit secrets\n- Use .env files locally\n- Use secrets manager in production'''\n    },\n    # === 数据处理 ===\n    {\n        'signals': ['database', 'sql', 'query'],\n        'title': 'SQL Query Optimization',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.93,\n        'streak': 11,\n        'content': '''## Problem\nSlow queries block the entire application.\n\n## Solution\n- Add indexes on WHERE/JOIN columns\n- Avoid SELECT *\n- Use EXPLAIN ANALYZE\n- Implement query caching\n\n```sql\n-- Before: 5s\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE user_id = 123;\n\n-- After: 50ms\nSELECT id, status, total FROM orders \nWHERE user_id = 123 \nAND created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days';\n\n-- Index\nCREATE INDEX idx_orders_user_date ON orders(user_id, created_at);\n```\n## Benefits\n- 100x faster queries\n- Reduced DB load\n- Better scalability'''\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['json', 'parse', 'serialize'],\n        'title': 'Efficient JSON Processing',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.89,\n        'streak': 8,\n        'content': '''## Problem\nJSON parsing is slow for large payloads.\n\n## Solution\n- Use orjson (Rust-based, 3x faster)\n- Stream parse for large files\n- Cache parsed results\n\n```python\n\n[343 more lines in file. Use offset=340 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773850382916}}
